<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="756" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-28"><hi rend="italic">January 28,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. McCormick requests to be informed whether the affidavits mentioned
                            in his telegram of the 11th instant have been forwarded.)</p>
                    </div>
